scenes.title: Make Popsicles!
scenes.content: Start by plugging all twelve (12) long red pentagonal struts into blue balls.

scenes.title: Build Spikeball
scenes.content: Build using only long red (pentagonal) struts and blue balls on the ends. Plug them all into a white ball in the center.

scenes.title: Build Spikeball
scenes.content: Build using only long red (pentagonal) struts and blue balls on the ends. Plug them all into a white ball in the center.

scenes.title: Bridge Each Blue Ball
scenes.content: Bridge each blue ball with a long blue rectangular strut.

scenes.title: The Icosahedron
scenes.content: Continue bridging blue balls with blue struts to make the Icosahedron, a regular 20-sided solid object!

scenes.title: Remove Center
scenes.content: Remove the center of your new icosahedron.  This is the strongest shape such a small virus has evolved to make. Continue to explore the symmetries of this object.

scenes.title: 2-Fold Symmetry Setup
scenes.content: Place a blue strut in any hole of any ball of the model.

scenes.title: 2-fold Shadow
scenes.content: Point the strut directly at the sun and notice its shadow line up to reveal the symmetry!

scenes.title: 3-Fold Symmetry Setup
scenes.content: Place a yellow strut in any hole of any ball of the model.

scenes.title: 3-fold Shadow
scenes.content: Point the strut directly at the sun and notice its shadow line up to reveal the symmetry!

scenes.title: 5-fold Shadow
scenes.content: Point the strut directly at the sun and notice its shadow line up to reveal the symmetry!

scenes.title: Start DNA section
scenes.content: The first coil of the DNA in the virus is inserted here. We shall see how it is constructed..

scenes.title: View - Hiding highlighted struts
scenes.content: We're hiding the highlighted struts to see how the DNA is constructed.

scenes.title: Icosa Hidden, Viewing Setup
scenes.content: Notice which hole the short B0 strut is in, and which holes the white R00 struts plug into. Copy that carefully.

scenes.title: View along DNA axis
scenes.content: Notice the pseudo-hexagon made with the white R00s while looking down the blue (2-fold) axis.

scenes.title: Continue the coils
scenes.content: Continue the coils until all R00s (32x) are used.

scenes.title: Spring until it fits
scenes.content: Plug the B0 into the other hole.
